-- Mexico Stocks: Alfa, America Movil, Comerci, Femsa Advance
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-01-16T22:02:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-16/mexico-stocks-alfa-america-movil-comerci-femsa-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC  index  rose 1 percent to 36,916.16.  Mexican stocks followed European equities higher as  France 
auctioned debt at a lower borrowing cost, even after Standard &
Poor’s stripped the country of its top  credit rating .  Controladora Comercial Mexicana SAB (COMERUBC)  , a
Mexican supermarket chain, gained 4 percent to 26.21 pesos.
 Fomento Economico Mexicano SAB (FEMSAUBD)  , Latin America’s
largest Coca-Cola bottler, rose 1.1 percent to 92.98 pesos.
 America Movil SAB (AMXL)  , the wireless carrier controlled by
billionaire Carlos Slim, rose 1.1 percent to 15.30 pesos.  Alfa SAB (ALFAA)  , Mexico’s largest privately-owned
chemical company, jumped 8.6 percent to 170.99 pesos. Its Alpek
SA unit filed for a possible initial public offering, according
to a statement sent Jan. 13 after markets had closed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
